==English==
===Verb===

#To assemble a mechanical and/or electrical device in a hasty, low-quality manner, especially when cheap, low-quality and/or inapproprate materials are used.
#To assemble a mechanical and/or electrical device in a fundamentally unsafe manner, usually in such a way that the device is doomed to failure (sometimes catastrophic failure).
#To fix a mechanical or electrical device in the above manners.

Past-tense:  Jerryrigged

(Note:  This word only applies to mechanical and/or electrical devices.  Inanimate objects built in the above manner are said to by [[jerrybuild|jerrybuilt]].)